    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.5.8-9_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">8</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        Carmel
                        4 Feb 18
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear John Neihardt, &#8212;</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am glad indeed to have it settled that you are to come here from Stanford, to stay till it is time for you to go to Berkely. We will have a glorious time together making over the world if you want to, or reconciling it if it turns out that way. If only the weather will be kind while you are here, and we have a few of our Carmel
                
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.5.8-9_0002b"/>
                
                    sunsets, I'll bet on the reconciliation, but not to the extent of taking the zip out of life. &#8212; In coming to this <unclear>slightly</unclear> off the <unclear>map place</unclear> from Palo Alto you take the train to Monterey; from which, at the station, you take the automobile bus to our house in Carmel &#8212; a fifteen to twenty minute ride. Better let me know what train to expect you on and I will meet you at Monterey. We are all on tiptoe with anti-
                
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.5.8-9_0002a"/>
                
                    cipation of your coming. I hope you'll have a fine trip on.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Cordially yours</salute>
                    
                    <signed>John Howard</signed>
                    <note type="curatorial">Howard</note>
                </closer>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">9</fw>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
